Anonymous Wed 01 Jul 2020 12:12:07 No.31239830 Report
Quoted By: >>31239929 >>31240184
>>31239375
>To that effect, any chance for some rough plot ideas? I'm thinking of having it be between some human trainer and his renamon partner
A important distinction between something like Pokémon and Digimon Tamers, is the digimon are the one's picking partners, not the other way around. So there's a multitude of ways you could go about your protagonist and Renamon interacting, given the digital realm is basically the internet.
>Anon (for the sake of these examples) finds a old dead digivice at a Goodwill, and after a ton of troubleshooting with it at home, finally figures out how to interface with it, causing its original occupant to find it again through the 'net...
>As anon is digging through old archives on some obscure Japanese website, he comes across some old executables that won't boot on a modern machine, so he pulls out his trusty late 90's test rig to see what it does...
>After picking it up at a auction from some old Japanese guy that died recently, anon tries to dump the contents of a old half broken digivice to his computer, to which the data is miraculously finally freed from its previously mangled state...
If you know a lot about how computing was in the late 90's/early 2000's, or generally hobbyist electronics in the current year, I'd definitely lean on that kind of knowledge for a plot as digimon are literally just physicalized data, which is in part why the digivices are fairly important as that's the main way partners interface with the digimon data, though the digimon aren't necessarily tied to a digivice or anything.
